For the binding definition of `SKSize`, `GetHashCode` is defined as 

```
	public override int GetHashCode ()
		{
			return (int) width ^ (int) height;
		}
```

However, this is incorrect. `Size(10, 10)` and `Size(10.99, 10.99)` will provide the same hash code in this instance.

I have a PR ready, but I presume, this bug also will remain across the definitions. Will probably give it a glance to see if more changes are required with other binding that accept float/double before submitting.
